Naza BarkPack Small-Size Vocal Capability Idea Tree
version: 2026-07-07
goal: keep Bark/Convo packs small while pushing closer to human, word-like, Bark-inspired voice generation
constraint: target laptops with ~8 GB RAM, fast CPU path, optional GPU, secure SHA-verified downloadable packs

palette
├─ #55E6A5 mint        = semantic / linguistic structure
├─ #8EC5FF sky         = speaker identity / voice color
├─ #FFC857 gold        = codec / compression / quantization
├─ #FF7A66 coral       = naturalness / prosody / expressiveness
├─ #B18CFF violet      = neural distillation / tiny models
├─ #6EE7F9 cyan        = runtime scheduler / speed
├─ #F5A3FF rose        = long-form continuity / conversation memory
├─ #A3FF8F lime        = safety / validation / anti-corruption
└─ #D6D9DE silver      = challenge / risk / test gate

root: "small pack, better speech"
├─ seed_ideas[15]
│  ├─ 01_mini_semantic_tokenizer #55E6A5
│  │  ├─ idea: add a tiny grapheme/phoneme/syllable tokenizer that turns script words into Bark-like semantic events.
│  │  ├─ size_plan: rules + compact exception table, not a large tokenizer model.
│  │  └─ why: current humming improves only when events match word rhythm and vowel/consonant structure.
│  ├─ 02_speaker_embedding_sidecars #8EC5FF
│  │  ├─ idea: store a few tiny speaker vectors sidecar-style: pitch range, breath, brightness, nasality, pace.
│  │  ├─ size_plan: 32-128 float/int8 values per voice.
│  │  └─ why: sidecars give stable identity without shipping large history prompts.
│  ├─ 03_phoneme_formant_micro_lut #FFC857
│  │  ├─ idea: ship a small phoneme-to-formant lookup table with vowel/consonant envelopes.
│  │  ├─ size_plan: hundreds of bytes to a few KB.
│  │  └─ why: makes generated audio sound articulated rather than a smooth buzz.
│  ├─ 04_tiny_prosody_predictor #B18CFF
│  │  ├─ idea: distill punctuation, word length, emotion tags, and speaker into pitch/duration/energy curves.
│  │  ├─ size_plan: tiny MLP, decision trees, or quantized linear tables.
│  │  └─ why: prosody is a large part of human-likeness and does not require full Bark weights.
│  ├─ 05_codebook_residual_texture #FFC857
│  │  ├─ idea: store a compressed residual texture codebook for breath, fricatives, plosives, and room tone.
│  │  ├─ size_plan: VQ table under 1-4 MB.
│  │  └─ why: speech realism often comes from noise detail, not just tonal formants.
│  ├─ 06_distilled_bark_semantic_decoder #B18CFF
│  │  ├─ idea: train a small student to approximate Bark semantic token timing from text.
│  │  ├─ size_plan: 5-30 MB int4/int8.
│  │  └─ why: gets closer to Bark behavior without shipping original-scale models.
│  ├─ 07_lpcnet_style_vocoder_lane #FFC857
│  │  ├─ idea: use an LPC/formant source-filter vocoder plus tiny neural/noise excitation.
│  │  ├─ size_plan: tiny runtime, few MB tables/model.
│  │  └─ why: strong speech quality per byte on CPU.
│  ├─ 08_chunked_longform_voice_state #F5A3FF
│  │  ├─ idea: keep rolling speaker/prosody state between chunks so long replies do not reset voice.
│  │  ├─ size_plan: runtime state only, nearly zero pack cost.
│  │  └─ why: continuity makes voices feel much more human.
│  ├─ 09_adaptive_quality_layers #6EE7F9
│  │  ├─ idea: split pack into base voice + optional quality shards: consonants, emotion, room, studio harmonics.
│  │  ├─ size_plan: download only what profile needs.
│  │  └─ why: keeps default install small and allows upgrades.
│  ├─ 10_int4_groupwise_quantization #FFC857
│  │  ├─ idea: move selected tensors/side models from int8 to groupwise int4 with scale blocks.
│  │  ├─ size_plan: 30-50% smaller than int8 for supported lanes.
│  │  └─ why: frees budget for better semantic/speaker data.
│  ├─ 11_phrase_cache_and_reuse #6EE7F9
│  │  ├─ idea: cache rendered common phrases, phoneme curves, and speaker envelopes.
│  │  ├─ size_plan: local cache, not release size.
│  │  └─ why: faster iteration and smoother UI without bigger downloads.
│  ├─ 12_emotion_control_tokens #FF7A66
│  │  ├─ idea: compact emotion tags map to pitch, pace, breath, pause, and intensity curves.
│  │  ├─ size_plan: small JSON/table.
│  │  └─ why: expressive control can hide model limitations.
│  ├─ 13_multiband_noise_shaper #FF7A66
│  │  ├─ idea: synthesize fricative/breath noise in bands: s, sh, f, h, plosive pop, mouth click.
│  │  ├─ size_plan: no model or tiny LUT.
│  │  └─ why: makes words more recognizable.
│  ├─ 14_runtime_probe_quality_score #A3FF8F
│  │  ├─ idea: probe installed pack for all families, sidecars, version, tensor counts, and estimated quality.
│  │  ├─ size_plan: metadata only.
│  │  └─ why: prevents "installed but humming" confusion.
│  └─ 15_micro_mel_to_wave_decoder #B18CFF
│     ├─ idea: generate a tiny mel-like acoustic frame stream, then decode with a small quantized vocoder.
│     ├─ size_plan: 15-60 MB depending quality.
│     └─ why: highest realistic jump toward human sound while staying below full Bark size.

loops
├─ loop_01 expand #55E6A5
│  ├─ build: add syllable nuclei detection to 01, not just word events.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: English-only rules may sound wrong for names, code, acronyms, and slang.
│  └─ mutate: add a fallback character n-gram phoneme guesser and "spell-out" mode for unknown tokens.
├─ loop_02 expand #8EC5FF
│  ├─ build: make 02 speaker sidecars include pitch contour bias and consonant softness.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: tiny vectors can collapse voices into caricatures.
│  └─ mutate: store two profiles per voice: calm and intense, interpolate by emotion tokens.
├─ loop_03 expand #FFC857
│  ├─ build: combine 03 and 13 into a "mouth events" table: vowel, nasal, stop, fricative, liquid, glide.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: formant tables alone can sound robotic.
│  └─ mutate: add random-but-seeded micro-variation per syllable so repeated words do not clone themselves.
├─ loop_04 expand #B18CFF
│  ├─ build: train 04 tiny prosody predictor from generated Bark clips: text features -> duration/pitch/energy.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: training data may be large and licensing-sensitive.
│  └─ mutate: generate synthetic training data from user-owned prompts and store only distilled weights.
├─ loop_05 expand #FFC857
│  ├─ build: make 05 residual texture codebook phoneme-conditioned.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: codebooks can add noise but not intelligibility.
│  └─ mutate: use texture only at consonant boundaries; leave vowels clean and formant-driven.
├─ loop_06 expand #B18CFF
│  ├─ build: 06 student model predicts semantic token classes, not raw audio.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: if output token space is fake, it may not improve sound.
│  └─ mutate: define Naza semantic tokens as practical speech events: onset, vowel, consonant, pause, emphasis.
├─ loop_07 expand #FFC857
│  ├─ build: 07 LPC lane uses pitch pulses plus filtered noise, not sine-only tone.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: LPC tuning can be brittle across voices.
│  └─ mutate: make speaker sidecar hold stable LPC coefficients per voice color.
├─ loop_08 expand #F5A3FF
│  ├─ build: 08 stores rolling "conversation breath" so pauses and intensity continue between chunks.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: long state can drift into monotony.
│  └─ mutate: reset only micro-state at paragraph boundaries, keep speaker identity state.
├─ loop_09 expand #6EE7F9
│  ├─ build: 09 splits BarkPack into base.pack, voice.pack, clarity.pack, studio.pack.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: multiple downloads complicate SHA verification and UI.
│  └─ mutate: one manifest, many optional shards, each with independent SHA and family contribution.
├─ loop_10 expand #FFC857
│  ├─ build: 10 stores int4 blocks for side models but leaves tiny tables uint8/raw for simple loading.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: int4 decode can cost CPU and add bugs.
│  └─ mutate: implement int4 only for large neural tables, never for hot tiny LUTs.
├─ loop_11 expand #6EE7F9
│  ├─ build: 11 caches semantic events separately from WAV output.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: cache invalidation can cause mismatched voice/profile.
│  └─ mutate: cache key includes pack SHA, speaker vector hash, preset, language, and renderer version.
├─ loop_12 expand #FF7A66
│  ├─ build: 12 maps "whisper, excited, tired, radio, close mic" to deterministic render coefficients.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: too many knobs make UI confusing.
│  └─ mutate: expose simple style prompt; internal parser maps text to hidden controls.
├─ loop_13 expand #FF7A66
│  ├─ build: 13 models sibilants as high-band filtered noise envelopes.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: too much high-band noise becomes hissy.
│  └─ mutate: tie noise gain to vowel energy and clamp by speaker brightness.
├─ loop_14 expand #A3FF8F
│  ├─ build: 14 quality score shows "acoustic-only", "sidecar speech", "neural-lite", "full graph".
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: quality labels may overpromise.
│  └─ mutate: show exact capabilities: semantic sidecar yes/no, speaker sidecar yes/no, vocoder type.
├─ loop_15 expand #B18CFF
│  ├─ build: 15 tiny mel decoder uses 80-bin frames at low fps, then CPU vocoder.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: mel decoder may still be too big for 140 MB budget.
│  └─ mutate: optional "voice clarity shard" adds the decoder only when user wants larger download.
├─ loop_16 recombine #55E6A5
│  ├─ build: combine 01 + 06: rules produce initial semantic tokens, student model refines timing/emphasis.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: two systems can disagree.
│  └─ mutate: student only outputs deltas, never replaces safe rule baseline.
├─ loop_17 recombine #8EC5FF
│  ├─ build: combine 02 + 07: speaker vector controls source-filter parameters.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: voice identity may be too synthetic.
│  └─ mutate: add tiny per-voice residual texture from 05 for organic variation.
├─ loop_18 recombine #FFC857
│  ├─ build: combine 05 + 10: quantize residual texture with product quantization.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: compressed artifacts may buzz.
│  └─ mutate: use residual texture only above 2 kHz and during consonants.
├─ loop_19 recombine #F5A3FF
│  ├─ build: combine 08 + 11: long-form semantic cache stores rolling state and avoids recomputing chunks.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: disk cache can grow.
│  └─ mutate: LRU cache capped by MB and expires by pack SHA.
├─ loop_20 recombine #FF7A66
│  ├─ build: combine 12 + 13: emotion controls consonant sharpness and breath.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: emotional speech can become noisy.
│  └─ mutate: emotion intensity has a "naturalness governor" that avoids extremes unless studio mode.
├─ loop_21 challenge #D6D9DE
│  ├─ concern: sidecar semantic/speaker families satisfy manifest gates but do not equal true Bark inference.
│  ├─ hard_truth: they improve structure only if the renderer consumes them deeply.
│  └─ new_idea #B18CFF: create "sidecar v2" with learned coefficients, not just metadata hashes.
├─ loop_22 challenge #D6D9DE
│  ├─ concern: full neural Bark quality probably cannot fit in tiny size without serious distillation.
│  ├─ hard_truth: 140-240 MB can be good, but not magic.
│  └─ new_idea #B18CFF: train a 30-80 MB Bark-lite model specifically for Naza semantic tokens.
├─ loop_23 challenge #D6D9DE
│  ├─ concern: CPU-only real-time vocoding is the bottleneck on 8 GB laptops.
│  ├─ hard_truth: tiny neural vocoders can still spike CPU.
│  └─ new_idea #6EE7F9: render low-rate semantic/prosody first, stream audio in small chunks, cache finished chunks.
├─ loop_24 challenge #D6D9DE
│  ├─ concern: better word intelligibility may require phoneme dictionaries.
│  ├─ hard_truth: dictionaries cost size but rules miss edge cases.
│  └─ new_idea #55E6A5: include a compressed top-20k pronunciation lexicon shard as optional "clarity-en".
├─ loop_25 mutate #55E6A5
│  ├─ build: add language packs: base English rules in app, optional lexicon shards by language.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: multi-language expands scope quickly.
│  └─ mutate: support language tags but ship only one default compact language.
├─ loop_26 mutate #8EC5FF
│  ├─ build: generate speaker sidecars from a short local calibration phrase.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: privacy and consent must be explicit.
│  └─ mutate #A3FF8F: store calibration locally only, never upload; hash/cache with user control.
├─ loop_27 mutate #FFC857
│  ├─ build: add "codec shimmer" table sampled from verified pack fingerprints.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: fingerprint-derived audio texture is not real learned audio.
│  └─ mutate: use it as subtle modulation only, not primary sound source.
├─ loop_28 mutate #B18CFF
│  ├─ build: distill a micro duration model: text token features -> milliseconds.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: bad duration ruins intelligibility.
│  └─ mutate: clamp model output with rule-based min/max per phoneme class.
├─ loop_29 mutate #FF7A66
│  ├─ build: add "mouth closure" plosive model: silence dip + pressure burst.
│  ├─ challenge #D6D9DE: plosives can clip.
│  └─ mutate: normalize burst energy through limiter before codec stage.
├─ loop_30 mutate #F5A3FF
│  ├─ build: assign per-character voice memory in conversations: narrator, speaker_a, speaker_b.
