ranked_next_build_candidates
├─ quick_win_01 #55E6A5: implement compact phoneme/syllable event generator in native/Dart.
├─ quick_win_02 #FF7A66: improve consonant/fricative/plosive envelopes in current FFI renderer.
├─ quick_win_03 #8EC5FF: make speaker sidecars carry real voice coefficients, not only deterministic markers.
├─ quick_win_04 #A3FF8F: add BarkPack quality label and self-test result in Settings/Bark tab.
├─ medium_01 #B18CFF: train tiny prosody/duration student model and ship int8.
├─ medium_02 #FFC857: add residual texture codebook under 4 MB.
├─ medium_03 #F5A3FF: rolling voice state for long-form chunk continuity.
├─ large_01 #B18CFF: BarkLite semantic decoder, 30-80 MB, optional shard.
└─ large_02 #B18CFF: micro mel-to-wave decoder, optional 60-200 MB quality tier.

hard_constraints_to_keep_rechecking
├─ size #FFC857: every added shard needs before/after MB cost and SHA pin.
├─ cpu #6EE7F9: no hot path should block Flutter UI isolate.
├─ truthfulness #A3FF8F: sidecars are not full neural Bark; UI should label capabilities honestly.
├─ security #A3FF8F: all packs stay HTTPS + SHA-256 verified + sanitized filenames.
└─ quality #FF7A66: judge by intelligible words, not just "less hum".

continuation_loops
